"(1) (i) The metallic clang of an alarm shattered the morning calm of the deep-basement maintenance tunnels. Julian’s breath caught as the red emergency strobes flickered overhead, painting the concrete walls in violent crimson. Through the thick glass of his security monitor, he saw the reactor core’s secondary containment—marked with faded warnings in archaic English—shudder violently. A low, oscillating hum rose, vibrating through the floor, as if the very earth was holding its breath. He pressed his back against the cold steel doorframe, heart hammering, as the warning klaxons crescendoed into a deafening howl. Somewhere beyond the reinforced bulkhead, a pressure gauge spun wildly, its needle tearing through the scale with a sickening velocity.\n(2) (i) watched in horror as a brilliant arc of blue-white plasma erupted from a fractured conduit, twisting through the air like a living bolt. The sudden surge of superheated gas hissed and exploded against the containment wall, fracturing the metal with a symphony of crackling sounds. Sparks rained down, illuminating the sterile corridors with a harsh, clinical light. His mind raced with the implications—containment failure meant catastrophic release, but he could only stand frozen, separated from the chaos by a thick door and the thin barrier of protocol. Outside the sealed chamber, the air shimmered with residual energy, and the base itself seemed to tremble, as if it too knew what was about to come. Phobos Military Base. May 14, 2225. Julian Ross. witnessed a plasma conduit rupture."